$interpreted:
Leah: ...*sigh* ... So annoying, what are the chances, just so happened to be busted by the headmaster! 
Now I'm stuck here looking for some stupid root.
Leah: Where the heck am I going to find it...
Leah: ...Hmm?
Leah: This scent...although it's weak, it smells exactly like the sample headmaster showed me.
Leah: Hoho,  looks like it's located on the east side of the forest. My nose is awesome.
Leah: ...Just like back in the Slums. Every time something was missing, I would look for it with my nose.
Leah: Then Lio would always be by my side...
Annie: Lookie here, isn't this the smelly rabbit from the Slums?
Betty: What, already missing home? Then you should make haste and get your hairy butt back to the Slums!
Leah: Umm...why are you seniors here?

Cara: Just like you. got punished by the headmaster. 
Told us that we need to find the Tana Roots, or be expelled.
Annie: Shut it, you moron! You talk too much!
Leah: My dear seniors...I am very sorry for what happened in the morning.
Leah: Since Whistlewood Valley is really dangerous and that root seems to be very rare, can we work together?
Annie: Hmph, who in the right mind would work with you?
Leah: Pretty please~ us demihumans have a very keen sense of smell. I've caught the scent of the root just before we met.
Leah: It's to the west...
Leah: Oops, my bad, wrong direction. It's in the east, east side of the forest.
Cara: Was that a slip of the tongue just now?
Betty: Look at her, getting all shifty and nervous. It's definitely on the west side!
Annie: Then we'll go ahead and dig up all the roots before she can find them; that way she gets expelled!
Annie: Hmph, we'll be fine on our own. We don't need your help!
Betty: Yeah, now get out of our way!
Leah: Idiots, I told you it was the wrong direction. Have fun looking for nothing. Tehee.
Leah: Tch, why are the paths on the east side so difficult to walk on?
Leah: It really is dangerous here. I wonder if the seniors will be ok?
Leah: Why am I thinking about them now? What happens to them is none of my business!
